=== Retirement ===
{{seealso|List of retired Atlantic hurricanes}}
The [[World Meteorological Organization]] retired four names in the spring of 2005: Charley, Frances, Ivan, and Jeanne. They will be replaced in 2010 by Colin, Fiona, Igor, and Julia. The 2004 season was tied with the [[1955 Atlantic hurricane season|1955 season]] and [[1995 Atlantic hurricane season|1995 season]] for the most storm names retired after a single season until the [[2005 Atlantic hurricane season|2005 season]], when five names were retired.

